yǒu /you3/
1. to have; there is
2. (bound form) having; with; -ful; -ed; -al (as in »yǒuyì« intentional)
3. friend
4. black; dark green
5. 10th earthly branch: 5-7 p.m., 8th solar month (8th September-7th October), year of the Rooster; ancient Chinese compass point: 270° (west)
6. Setaria viridis; vicious
7. europium (chemistry)
8. wine container
9. grievous; relaxed
10. ritual bonfire
11. the vitreous glaze on china, porcelain etc
12. to enlighten; lattice window
13. to lead

2. cloud; CL: duǒ
3. even; well-distributed; uniform; to distribute evenly; to share
4. common rue (Ruta graveolens); (used in old compounds relating to books because in former times rue was used to protect books from insect damage)
5. sun light; used in personal name
6. rushing of a torrent
7. river waves
8. (yellow color)
9. reclaimed land
10. skin of bamboo
11. confused; numerous
12. to weed
13. name of a feudal state
14. gold
